<p>I'm trying to show or hide a <code>&lt;f:selectItem</code> of a <code>&lt;h:selectOneMenu</code> based on input from the server.</p>  <p>This is what I tried:</p>  <pre><code>&lt;h:panelGroup rendered="#{searchResults.showEndingSoonest()}" &gt;    &lt;f:selectItem itemLabel="About to End" itemValue="Ending" /&gt; &lt;/h:panelGroup&gt; </code></pre>  <p>and also </p>  <pre><code>&lt;f:selectItem itemLabel="About to End" itemValue="Ending" rendered="#{searchResults.showEndingSoonest()}"/&gt; </code></pre>  <p>but both aren't working, although <code>showEndingSoonest</code> is called and returns the correct value. Surely I can put the entire <code>&lt;h:selectOneMenu</code> block inside a <code>panelGroup</code> but maybe there's a more elegant solution? </p>